history.content: EECS 149 (capacity of 42) is room-shared with EE C249A (capacity of 20) and CS C249A (capacity of 14) making the total enrollment 76. Sometimes there are a extra seats in the secondary sections to give students more options.

children.subject: It most likely will not expand. If any of the 3 parts of the class don't fill however, those seats would go to the category that needs it, eg if the CS C249A seats don't fill, those would go to EECS 149.
So that means the size of lec won't expand?

history.content: On schedule builder, the opening seat capacity for EECS 149 right now is 13. However, when I add up all the remaining seats in lab sections, it is 46. Does this mean that the size for the lecture is going to expand as the lab seats exceed the lecture seats? If the lecture is full but there is still seats in the lab sections, can we add ourselves to the waitlist and be processed later on?
